=================


This is one of the most important code blocks in RAG. It is called Text Chunking (Document Splitting).

Code: Split Documents into Chunks using RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter

| Line No. | Code                                                                 | Purpose                                                                        | Output                                                      |
| -------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------- |
| **1**    | `from langchain.text_splitter import RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter` | Imports the **RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter** class from LangChain.           | Ready to split large documents into smaller chunks.         |
| **2**    | `text_splitter = RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter(`                    | Creates a **Text Splitter** object.                                            | Initializes the text splitting process.                     |
| **3**    | `chunk_size=1000,`                                                   | Sets the **maximum size** of each text chunk to **1000 characters**.           | Each chunk contains up to 1000 characters.                  |
| **4**    | `chunk_overlap=200`                                                  | Repeats the last **200 characters** from the previous chunk in the next chunk. | Preserves context between consecutive chunks.               |
| **5**    | `)`                                                                  | Completes the configuration of the text splitter.                              | Text splitter is ready for use.                             |
| **6**    | `documents = text_splitter.split_documents(docs)`                    | Splits the loaded PDF (`docs`) into multiple smaller document chunks.          | Creates a list of chunked `Document` objects.               |
| **7**    | `documents[:5]`                                                      | Displays the **first five document chunks**.                                   | Shows the first five chunks to verify successful splitting. |

=============

Parameter Explanation

| Parameter         | Value  | Meaning                                                | Why It Is Used                                                               |
| ----------------- | ------ | ------------------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **chunk_size**    | `1000` | Maximum number of characters in each chunk             | Prevents sending very large text to the embedding model and vector database. |
| **chunk_overlap** | `200`  | Number of characters shared between consecutive chunks | Preserves context when information spans two chunks.                         |

